  Option 1: Using defaults (simplest)
  system "defaults write ${plist} CFBundleIconFile bobcat"

  Option 2: Using /usr/libexec/PlistBuddy (more reliable)
  system "/usr/libexec/PlistBuddy -c 'Set :CFBundleIconFile bobcat' ${plist}"

  PlistBuddy is the most reliable option - it's been available since 10.5 and handles both adding and
  modifying keys well. If the key doesn't exist, you can use:
  system "/usr/libexec/PlistBuddy -c 'Add :CFBundleIconFile string bobcat' ${plist}"

  Or combine both (try Set, fall back to Add):
  system "/usr/libexec/PlistBuddy -c 'Set :CFBundleIconFile bobcat' ${plist} || /usr/libexec/PlistBuddy -c
   'Add :CFBundleIconFile string bobcat' ${plist}"